-- Canada's Harper Says in Bern That Currency Situation to Remain `Difficult'
-- B y   J e n n i f e r   M .   F r e e d m a n
-- 2010-10-22T11:18:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/canada-s-harper-says-in-bern-that-currency-situation-to-remain-difficult-.html
Canada’s Prime Minister Stephen
Harper said the situation on global currency markets will remain
“difficult.”   “A well-functioning, open global trading system needs
flexibility,” Harper told reporters at a press conference in
Bern, Switzerland, today after a meeting with Swiss President
Doris Leuthard.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer M. Freedman in Geneva at 
